outlier_counts <- sapply(df[,2:24], function(x) {
  qnt <- quantile(x, probs = c(.25, .75), na.rm = TRUE)
    caps <- qnt + c(-1.5, 1.5) * IQR(x, na.rm = TRUE)
  out <- x < caps[1] | x > caps[2]
  sum(out)
})

outlier_counts <- sapply(df_cleaned[,2], function(x) {
  qnt <- quantile(x, probs = c(.25, .75), na.rm = TRUE)
    caps <- qnt + c(-1.5, 1.5) * IQR(x, na.rm = TRUE)
  out <- x < caps[1] | x > caps[2]
  sum(out)
})

CHISQUARE TEST

#Observed Frequency
df_cleaned<-df_cleaned[,1:25]
observed<-df_cleaned%>%filter(default=="Yes")%>%group_by(SEX)%>%summarize(`Freq`=n())
observed<-data.frame(observed)
print(observed)
##      SEX Freq
## 1   MALE 2866
## 2 FEMALE 3751
#calculating expected frequency
p=c(rep(0.5,2))
p
## [1] 0.5 0.5
alpha=0.05
result<-chisq.test(observed$Freq,p=p)
print(result)
## 
##  Chi-squared test for given probabilities
## 
## data:  observed$Freq
## X-squared = 118.37, df = 1, p-value < 2.2e-16
ifelse(result$p.value>alpha,"Fail to reject H0","Reject H0")
## [1] "Reject H0"
#### chisquare for education level 

observed_1<-df_cleaned%>%filter(default=="Yes")%>%group_by(EDUCATION)%>%summarize(`Freq`=n())
observed_1<-data.frame(observed_1)
print(observed_1)
##     EDUCATION Freq
## 1    Graduate 2029
## 2  University 3320
## 3 High School 1236
## 4      Others   32
#calculating expected frequency
p1=c(rep(0.25,4))
p1
## [1] 0.25 0.25 0.25 0.25
alpha=0.05
result1<-chisq.test(observed_1$Freq,p=p1)
print(result1)
## 
##  Chi-squared test for given probabilities
## 
## data:  observed_1$Freq
